The '''1999 Dubai Tennis Championships''' was a [[tennis]] tournaments played on [[Hardcourt|outdoor hard courts]] at the [[Aviation Club Tennis Centre]] in [[Dubai]] in the [[United Arab Emirates]] that were part of the [[ATP International Series|World Series]] of the [[1999 ATP Tour]]. The tournament was held from February 8 through February 14, 1999.

==Champions==

===Singles===
{{main|1999 Dubai Tennis Championships – Singles}}
{{flagicon|FRA}} '''[[Jérôme Golmard]]''' defeated {{flagicon|GER}} [[Nicolas Kiefer]] 6–4, 6–2<ref>{{cite web|url= http://sportsillustrated.ca/tennis/news/1999/02/14/dubai_open/|title=Golmard defeats Kiefer at Dubai for first Tour win |date=14 February 1999|work=Sports Illustrated|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>
* It was Golmard's 1st title of the year and the 1st of his career.

===Doubles===
{{main|1999 Dubai Tennis Championships – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|ZIM}} '''[[Wayne Black]]''' / {{flagicon|AUS}} '''[[Sandon Stolle]]''' defeated {{flagicon|RSA}} [[David Adams (tennis)|David Adams]] / {{flagicon|RSA}} [[John-Laffnie de Jager]] 4–6, 6–1, 6–4<ref>{{cite web|url= http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/tennis/stats/1999/news.mendoubwin.html|title= 1999 ATP Tour Tennis Doubles Winners, Final Results, Earnings |date=21 November 1999|work=Sports Illustrated |accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>
* It was Black's 1st title of the year and the 1st of his career. It was Stolle's 1st title of the year and the 10th of his career.

